	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">S. D.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Commendo tibi, mi charissime <persName ref="p8418" cert="high">Myconi</persName>, hunc d. <persName ref="p1884" cert="high">Lavateri</persName> consulis<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Der "stillstehende" Bürgermeister <persName ref="p1888" cert="high">Hans Rudolf Lavater</persName>.</note> filium<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2"><persName ref="p1884" cert="high">Ludwig Lavater</persName>; s. unten Z. <ptr target="qvzl17301-3" type="qv"/>. - Das hier nicht näher ausgeführte Anliegen, mit dem Ludwig sich an den Basler Stadtschreiber <persName cert="high" type="citizen_name" ref="p2804">Heinrich Ryhiner</persName> wenden wollte, hat mit seinem geplanten Studienaufenthalt in <placeName ref="l378" cert="high">Paris</placeName> zu tun; s. <ref target="file13084">Nr. 3035</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17304-6" type="qv"/>. Dort studierte nämlich schon <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p2804" cert="high">Ryhiners</persName> Sohn <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p6310" cert="high">Johann Heinrich</persName>; s. <bibl>AK</bibl> VI 20f. Wir danken Rainer Henrich für letzteren Hinweis.<ptr target="zfnfn17301-2" type="zfn"/></note>, hominem doctum et pium, valde diligenter.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Iuva illum!</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ipse tibi, cur adsit, exponet.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div2" corresp="regest2">
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Spero te meas<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3"><persName type="citizen_name" ref="p495" cert="high">Bullingers</persName> Brief <ref target="file13069">Nr. 3020</ref> vom 23. September, dem Johannes Hallers Brief an Bullinger <ref target="file13054">Nr. 3005</ref> vom 9. September beigelegt war; s. <ref target="file13069">Nr. 3020</ref>, <ptr target="qvfn17288-1" type="qv"/>.</note> accepisse a <persName ref="p3559" cert="high">Hartmanno a Hallwyl</persName>.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Eas,<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Hier ist allein Hallers Brief gemeint.</note> uti in literis monui scriptis,<note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5">Siehe <ref target="file13069">Nr. 3020</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17288-2" type="qv"/>.</note> repeto.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Mitto his inclusas binas<note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6">Einer dieser beiden Briefe war Hallers Brief <ref target="file13066">Nr. 3017</ref> vom 20. September, wie aus <ref target="file13084">Nr. 3035</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17304-3" type="qv"/>, hervorgeht; der andere <persName ref="p8055" cert="high">Ambrosius Blarers</persName> Brief <ref target="file13072">Nr. 3023</ref> vom 29. September, wie aus <ref target="file13084">Nr. 3035</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17304-4" type="qv"/>, deutlich wird.<ptr target="zfnfn17301-1" type="zfn"/></note>, sed ea lege, ut per hunc<note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7"><persName ref="p1884" cert="high">Ludwig Lavater</persName>.</note> remittas.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Propter negotia non potui plura.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div3" corresp="regest3">
				<p>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Scripsit ad me d. <persName ref="p8032" cert="high">Dryander</persName><note xml:id="fn8" type="footnote" n="8"><persName ref="p8032" cert="high">Francisco de Enzinas</persName>. - Dessen hier angesprochener Brief ist nicht erhalten.</note> per <persName ref="p1227" cert="high">Froschoverum</persName> redeuntem a <placeName ref="l157" cert="high">Franckfordia</placeName>.<note xml:id="fn9" type="footnote" n="9">Von der Herbstbuchmesse.</note></s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Illum amicissime salutabis.</s>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Scribam illi,<note xml:id="fn10" type="footnote" n="10">Nur ein Brief Bullingers an <persName ref="p8032" cert="high">Enzinas</persName> (vom 31. August 1549 - Cambridge, Corpus Christi College, Ms. 119, Nr. 68, 183f) ist erhalten geblieben.</note> quamprimum licuerit per occu-<pb type="edition" next="527"/>pationes.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Valeat et <persName ref="p1278" cert="high">Gastius</persName>, a quo nondum accepi <persName ref="p18967" cert="high">Persium</persName>.<note xml:id="fn11" type="footnote" n="11">Siehe dazu <ref target="file13033">Nr. 2984</ref>, <ptr target="qvfn17249-6" type="qv"/>, und zuletzt <ref target="file13069">Nr. 3020</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17288-1" type="qv"/>.</note></s>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vale.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tiguri, 5. octobris circa 9. noctis 1547.</s>
					<s n="15" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Bullingerus.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div4" corresp="regest4">
				<p>
					<s n="16" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Salutem dicito archigrammateo vestro<note xml:id="fn12" type="footnote" n="12"><placeName ref="l28" cert="high">Basels</placeName> Stadtschreiber <persName cert="high" type="citizen_name" ref="p2804">Heinrich Ryhiner</persName>. - Siehe dazu oben <ptr target="qvfn17301-2" type="qv"/>.</note> et ora meo nomine, ut causam huius <persName ref="p1884" cert="high">Ludovici</persName> habeat commendatam.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="17" xml:lang="la" type="auto">D. <persName ref="p8418" cert="high">Myconio</persName> suo.</s>
					<s n="18" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><placeName ref="l28" cert="high">Basileae</placeName>.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
